OL,7,F"Funding must follow the patient, and
OL,8,Fwe need to see significant investment
OL,9,Fin general practice, following years
OL,10,Fof underfunding by successive
OL,11,Fgovernments, so we can deliver safe,
OL,12,Ftimely and appropriate care to our
OL,13,Fpatients close to home."
OL,15,FRachel Power, chief executive of the
OL,16,FPatients Association, welcomed the
OL,17,Fannouncement, and said it is a "step
OL,18,Fin the right direction" but that "the
OL,19,Fsuccess of the scheme will depend on
OL,20,Fgenuine partnership between patients,
OL,21,FGPs, and specialists".
